Your buttons should, first and foremost,
look and function like buttons, right?

5
00:00:16.612 --> 00:00:17.480
That's the biggest thing.

6
00:00:17.480 --> 00:00:18.744
There are different styles you can apply.

7
00:00:18.744 --> 00:00:21.720
You can have completely
perpendicular edges.

8
00:00:21.720 --> 00:00:23.780
You can have ones with small
amount of border radius.

9
00:00:23.780 --> 00:00:25.030
You can have full border radius.

10
00:00:25.030 --> 00:00:29.082
You could have a drop shadow, but they
need to look and function like a button.

11
00:00:31.233 --> 00:00:33.190
So we've got solid buttons.

12
00:00:33.190 --> 00:00:33.900
No surprise here.

13
00:00:33.900 --> 00:00:36.100
They're just filled with
a solid background.

14
00:00:36.100 --> 00:00:38.060
These are pretty industry standard.

15
00:00:38.060 --> 00:00:39.980
This is, you would look at this and
know it's a button.

16
00:00:41.610 --> 00:00:44.500
You might have heard of ghost buttons or
line buttons.

17
00:00:44.500 --> 00:00:46.940
That just means that they don't
have a solid background fill.

18
00:00:46.940 --> 00:00:51.820
I'm gonna show you an example of mine,
my secondary buttons are ghost buttons.

19
00:00:51.820 --> 00:00:54.540
Typically, the filled buttons are primary
buttons because they draw the most

20
00:00:54.540 --> 00:00:55.740
attention.

21
