course about style components,

43
00:02:07.170 --> 00:02:10.370
design systems, and
he talked about elevation.

44
00:02:10.370 --> 00:02:14.492
You can have an elevation, library,
utility function which is really fun and

45
00:02:14.492 --> 00:02:16.126
can give your buttons height.

46
00:02:16.126 --> 00:02:19.160
You can also implement the on hover and
focus to indicate a state change.

47
00:02:21.490 --> 00:02:22.720
Let's talk about labels.

48
00:02:22.720 --> 00:02:26.990
We all love uppercase text, but
it's really hard for our users to read.

49
00:02:26.990 --> 00:02:29.280
Much harder to read than title case.

50
00:02:29.280 --> 00:02:31.985
So if you can use title case,
I would recommend using title case.

51
00:02:31.985 --> 00:02:34.958
And your labels need to fit
with the color contrast ratio,

52
00:02:34.958 --> 00:02:36.421
they need to be accessible.

53
00:02:36.421 --> 00:02:39.942
So you can see those bottom one is
really hard for our users to see.

54
00:02:39.942 --> 00:02:45.520
It does not pass
the WCAG AA color contrast.

55
00:02:45.520 --> 00:02:48.380
And also when we're talking fonts for
this, make sure it's thick enough.

56
00:02:48.380 --> 00:02:51.460
If you have a very, very thin font,
it's not gonna be recognizable.

57
00:02:52.550 --> 00:02:56.472
The whole goal is if you were to turn
off the color and decrease contrast,

58
00:02:56.472 --> 00:02:59.512
you should still be able to
read your button and your UI.

59
00:03:02.214 --> 00:03:04.854
So buttons need to be large
enough to be clickable and

60
00:03:04.854 --> 00:03:07.340
accessible on mobile devices.

